cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their architecture design, which is primarily used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the significance of individual neurons and their role in producing the output, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, i.e., cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses game theory and probabilistic approaches, which are related to neural networks and their optimization, and hence, it can also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses network compression and interpretability, which can be related to natural language processing and computational linguistics, i.e., cs.CL (Computation and Language).
